{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|女|又|ls=ic|t1=woman|t2=hand}} – a hand capturing and ordering a woman around. {{och-l|女}} may also be phonetic.

Some oracle bone script forms (not depicted above) are {{liushu|p|adj=1|nocap=1}}, showing a person (probably a woman) with hands crossed at the back, as opposed to {{zh-l|*女}} which depicts a woman clasping her hands in front of the body.
